    {
      "id": "ffb54f77_27d56c68",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/sdc/components/sdc-be/resources/config/catalog-be/janusgraph.properties",
      "patchset_number": 22,
      "line": 3,
      "message": "For this whole file, I would propose a more or less one-to-one mapping:\n`storage.port` -> `.Values.janusgraph.storage.cassandraPort`\n`storage.cql.ssl.enabled` -> `.Values.janusgraph.cql.ssl.enabled`\n`cache.db-cache` -> `.Values.janusgraph.cache.enabled`\n\nImportant for me is just that all Janusgraph related configs are grouped under a `janusgraph:` block in the `values.yaml`.\nHaving them all under `cassandra` is misleading from my point of view",
